  <title>Clutter.DeviceManager::device-added</title>
<synopsis><code mime="text/x-python">
def callback(device_manager, device, user_param1, ...)
</code></synopsis>
<p>The ::device-added signal is emitted each time a device has been
added to the <link xref="Clutter.DeviceManager">Clutter.DeviceManager</link></p>

<table>
<tr>
<td><p>device_manager :</p></td>
<td><p>instance of Clutter.DeviceManager that is emitting the signal</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>device :</p></td>
<td><p>the newly added <link xref="Clutter.InputDevice">Clutter.InputDevice</link></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>user_param1 :</p></td>
<td><p>first user parameter (if any) specified with the connect() method</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>... :</p></td>
<td><p>additional user parameters (if any)</p></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Since 1.2</p>
</page>
